11.  Scope of work. The subregional project manager's tasks will include but not be limited 
to the following: 
(i)  oversee the invitation, selection, and implementation of subprojects in Central 
Asia and in the Caucasus;  
(ii)  participate in the selection and implementation of subprojects in Kazakhstan 
(iii)  write project proposals for Kazakhstan for possible funding  
(iv)  coordinate country learning seminars in the region; 
(v)  convene  and  facilitate  project  management  team  meetings,  identify  potential 
members  of  focal  groups,  organize  the  groups,  and  maintain  working 
relationships with focal group members; 
(vi)  review and recommend for approval the outputs of national and international 
consultants under the subregional project management team; 
(vii)  work with the national GAD consultants on the CGA for Armenia and Georgia, 
and prepare the reports for publication; 
(viii)  update existing CGA as needed and provide input for CPS; 
(ix)  work with the national GAD consultants on the pilot-project reports and finalize 
the report for publication; 
(x)  provide technical support to national consultants and the TA technical committee;  
(xi)  provide  technical  support  to  prepare  national  and  regional  learning  events, 
including  strengthening  sex-disaggregated  statistics  in  national  statistical 
systems; 
(xii)  establish and support CWRD gender network in Central Asia and Caucasus 
region; 
(xiii)  help the TA coordinator to prepare TA reports; 
(xiv)  coordinate and plan with other GAD consultants of this project the inception 
meeting, midterm seminar, and end-of-project conference; 
(xv)  assist ADB project officers in preparing and implementing gender action plans 
and design and monitoring frameworks; and 
(xvi)  take the role of an implementation consultant in Kazakhstan. 

4.  Implementation Consultants (8 individuals, total of 168 person-months) 
12.  Objective/purpose of the assignment. The implementation consultants will implement 
the project at the country level. Their tasks will be to implement and monitor project gender 
action plans and TA subprojects and activities that contribute to the preparation of the CGA, 
including those that improve the capacity of the DMC to collect sex-disaggregated data.  

13.  Scope of work. The consultants’ tasks will include but not be limited to the following:   
(i)  guide  national  agencies  in  sex-disaggregated  data  collection  and  undertake 
activities  that  will  enable  DMC  partners  to  collect  and  maintain  a  sex-
disaggregated database; 
(ii)  collect baseline data on gender gaps in the assigned country; 
(iii)  participate in the selection of subprojects for gender mainstreaming;  
(iv)  write project proposals for possible funding; 
(v)  monitor the implementation of subprojects and ensure the delivery of high-quality 
outputs; 
(vi)  assist ADB project officers in preparing and implementing gender action plans 
and design and monitoring frameworks; 
(vii)  organize country gender focal groups; 
(viii)  lead regular meetings of country gender focal groups; 
(ix)  assist the subregional consultant in preparing the CGA for Armenia and Georgia;
